eld, 2 years experience in strategic planning and project management, knowledge of Microsoft Project Professional 2003 and Enterprise Project Management (EPM) System, and have a demonstrated ability to use analytical skills to excel in a fast-paced, multi-priority environment. &nbsp;Candidates should have strong verbal and written communication skills, proven ability to develop and manage project timelines effectively, strong leadership and facilitation skills, and a strong customer service orientation. &nbsp;Ideal candidates have project management experience in a technology-related field, preferably software development.<br>            <BR>            <B>Customer Service Representative<BR>            </B>Responsible for providing outstanding software support to GlobalTec&#8482; customers. &nbsp;Qualified applicants have customer service orientation, telephone support experience, proficiency with Microsoft&reg; Office, have exhibited a strong understanding of computers, and have demonstrated an ability to work in a fast paced environment. &nbsp;Ideal candidates have experience with GlobalTec products, an understanding of financial markets, and a business background.<BR>&nbsp;<BR><B>Developer<BR></B>Seeking a senior level Windows developer with expertise in developing and maintaining visually appealing client applications using MS Visual C++/MFC. Qualified candidates are skilled in creating custom drawn displays using the GDI and have a thorough understanding of the MFC Document/View architecture. &nbsp;Requirements include 8+ years Windows development experience, 6+ years MS Visual C++ experience, 5+ years recent experience using MFC with a focus on GUIs, 3+ years experience using the STL, and 2+ years experience with multi-threading. &nbsp;Ideal candidates are detail oriented with strong testing discipline and excellent verbal and written communication skills. &nbsp;Experience with COM/ATL is a plus.<br><BR><B>GlobalTec Trainer<BR></B>Responsible for supporting Instructors with all areas of training classes. &nbsp;Responsibilities include set up of training classes, one-on-one instruction, and product sales. &nbsp;Qualified candidates have outstanding verbal and written communication skills, comprehensive computer skills, the ability to work with diverse groups, and experience in sales. &nbsp;Knowledge in one of the following a plus: stocks, options, foreign currencies or commodities. Position requires approximately 50% travel.</SPAN></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, Arial"><FONT SIZE="5"><SPAN STYLE='font-size:16.0px'><BR>            <BR>            </SPAN></FONT><FONT SIZE="4"><SPAN STYLE='font-size:13.0px'><B>Technical Support Representative<BR>            </B>Responsible for troubleshooting hardware and software issues via telephone, e-mail and live chat for GlobalTec&#8482; customers to maintain continued customer satisfaction. &nbsp;Qualified applicants have 3 to 5 years technical support experience to include a working knowledge of Microsoft&reg; Windows environments (98, 2000, ME, XP), anti-virus software, firewalls, other software applications related to Internet connectivity and security, and various computer hardware. &nbsp;To be considered for the position, candidates must have solid organizational and time management skills, outstanding interpersonal skills, excellent verbal and written communication skills, strong problem solving ability, and a willingness to work any schedule including nights, weekends and holidays. &nbsp;Ideal candidates have MCSE, MCP, A+ certification, computer science degree or equivalent experience in the computer/technical support environment. &nbsp;<BR>            <BR>            <B>UNIX/FIX Developer<BR>            </B>Seeking an experienced UNIX software developer with experience designing, developing, and maintaining high availability financial trading systems using FIX. Qualified candidates have 4+ years experience developing server-side software on UNIX platforms, 4+ years C++ programming experience, competency in OOD/OOP principles and common design patterns, strong testing discipline, good understanding of basic UNIX systems administration, and meticulous attention to detail. &nbsp;Ideal candidates have experience with Solaris, Linux, ACE, and QuickFix, excellent verbal and written communication skills, and a demonstrated ability to be a self-starter with outstanding time management skills. &nbsp;A Bachelors degree in Computer Science or a related field or equivalent work experience is required.</SPAN></FONT></FONT> </p>            <p><FONT FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, Arial"><FONT FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, Arial"><FONT SIZE="4"><SPAN STYLE='font-size:13.0px'><BR>              <B><BR>              <BR>              </B></SPAN></FONT><SPAN STYLE='font-size:12.0px'><BR>                        </SPAN></FONT> <FONT SIZE="4"><SPAN STYLE='font-size:13.0px'><BR>            </SPAN></FONT></FONT> </p>            <p>&nbsp;</p></td>        </tr>      </table> </td>  </tr></table></body></html>